It might sound like a good idea, but when he tried to get politicians to use it,

00:06:38.948 --> 00:06:45.238
they didn’t even want to try, and the invention was a complete flop, it went nowhere.

00:06:46.438 --> 00:06:53.878
Edison swore to himself that from now on, he would not waste anymore time inventing things that

00:06:53.878 --> 00:07:01.108
people simply didn't want, and instead, he would focus on things that he knew people needed.

00:07:02.138 --> 00:07:08.338
But in order to move on with his inventions, Edison needed cash, he needed money.

00:07:09.048 --> 00:07:16.158
He moved to New York and was put up by a fellow telegrapher and inventor friend, Franklin Pope.

00:07:17.478 --> 00:07:22.398
When Edison fixed a broken machine for Pope, he was given a job managing

00:07:22.608 --> 00:07:26.668
and improving the printer machines at the Gold Indicator Company.

00:07:27.768 --> 00:07:32.178
During this period, Edison formed numerous partnerships and was

00:07:32.178 --> 00:07:35.988
involved in multiple projects all relating to the telegraph.

00:07:36.938 --> 00:07:43.858
Most notably, he set up an electrical engineering and invention company, Pope, Edison & Co

00:07:44.098 --> 00:07:50.308
and formed the American Telegraph Works, looking to develop an automatic telegraph system.

00:07:51.628 --> 00:08:00.538
Then, in 1874, when he was 27, Edison got his first big break, his first big financial success.

00:08:01.128 --> 00:08:04.318
He had invented the quadruplex telegraph.

00:08:05.218 --> 00:08:09.558
This type of telegraph allowed two signals to be sent in

00:08:09.558 --> 00:08:14.288
each direction, so four messages to be sent at the same time.

00:08:15.218 --> 00:08:22.118
Now, for you and me it might be hard to imagine a world in which communication was this difficult,

00:08:22.418 --> 00:08:29.578
and where being able to send dots along an electrical wire was such a groundbreaking achievement.

