00:17:11.859 --> 00:17:16.069
Edison had to take them off the market after a few short weeks.

00:17:17.069 --> 00:17:22.769
Now, it’s hard to be the most prolific inventor in the world if you spend too much time

00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:28.699
sitting around chatting to your friends, and for all of the potential criticisms one could

00:17:28.699 --> 00:17:34.509
make of Thomas Edison, you can’t say that he didn’t have a pretty formidable work ethic.

00:17:35.079 --> 00:17:40.799
He would work long hours at his laboratory and often stay up into the night, working away.

00:17:41.599 --> 00:17:45.679
One of his most famous quotes refers to his invention of the

00:17:45.689 --> 00:17:50.319
electric light bulb, which reportedly took him 10,000 attempts.

00:17:51.119 --> 00:17:54.549
He said: “I have not failed 10,000 times.

00:17:54.979 --> 00:17:56.249
I have not failed once.

00:17:56.669 --> 00:18:01.479
I have succeeded in proving that those 10,000 ways will not work.

00:18:02.449 --> 00:18:07.429
When I have eliminated the ways that will not work, I will find the way that will work.”

00:18:08.589 --> 00:18:14.129
This gives us some insight into Edison’s mind and what made him so successful.

00:18:15.089 --> 00:18:20.199
Unlike some geniuses with flashes of inspiration, such as Nikola

00:18:20.199 --> 00:18:25.899
Tesla, Edison was not afraid to plod away meticulously at his projects.

00:18:27.129 --> 00:18:32.529
This work ethic might have provided the country, and indeed the world, with

00:18:32.529 --> 00:18:37.789
some important inventions, but it certainly didn’t lead to a happy family life.

00:18:38.549 --> 00:18:45.049
He had a wife and a family, but his long days and nights at his laboratory, indeed often

00:18:45.059 --> 00:18:51.739
sleeping at the laboratory, meant that he rarely saw his family, and his first wife died

00:18:51.739 --> 00:18:58.879
of unknown causes, thought to be linked to stress and loneliness, before her 30th birthday.

00:18:59.989 --> 00:19:06.339
Following his first wife’s death, Edison continued to miss both lunch and dinner at home with

00:19:06.339 --> 00:19:12.609
his second wife and family, and continued to work long hours even right into his final days.

00:19:13.349 --> 00:19:16.629
In short, he was a complete workaholic.

00:19:17.369 --> 00:19:22.169
He even invented his own technique of power napping, a technique

00:19:22.309 --> 00:19:26.349
that he used to spend less time sleeping and more working.

00:19:27.389 --> 00:19:34.079
Edison would hold a heavy object in his hands and try to fall asleep while he was holding it.

00:19:34.960 --> 00:19:41.959
