00:20:57.737 --> 00:21:02.547
that much, but it would have made him one of the richest men in the country.

00:21:03.587 --> 00:21:09.867
Setting up his Menlo Park Laboratory or so called “invention factory” was certainly an

00:21:09.897 --> 00:21:16.147
inspirational and highly innovative venture that helped Edison to rise ahead of his rivals.

00:21:17.047 --> 00:21:21.957
Throughout his life, we can see how his ambition grew from his small

00:21:21.957 --> 00:21:26.237
beginnings selling newspapers and confectionery on trains to forming

00:21:26.247 --> 00:21:30.987
huge companies that are still around today, such as General Electric.

00:21:32.117 --> 00:21:38.297
Ultimately, Edison’s genius was to take all of these new, upcoming technologies, to

00:21:38.307 --> 00:21:44.037
